# üìò Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## **Product Name:** HeyBirdy

**Version:** 1.0 (Foundational PRD)
**Status:** Approved for Build
**Owner:** Product Team
**Target Launch:** MVP ‚Üí Public Beta

---

## 1. Product Overview

### 1.1 Product Vision

> **Turn passive fans into active growth partners so creators grow with people, not algorithms.**

HeyBirdy is a community-driven creator platform where:

* creators publish content,
* fans participate and share,
* affiliates earn by promoting,
* everyone is rewarded transparently.

---

### 1.2 Mission

> Build a single platform where content, community, monetization, and growth live together ‚Äî and where every contribution is rewarded.

---

## 2. Problem Statement

### 2.1 Creator Problems

* Algorithm-controlled reach (3‚Äì15%)
* High CAC ($5‚Äì15 per subscriber)
* Fragmented tools (5+ platforms)
* Passive audiences
* Unstable income

### 2.2 Audience Problems

* No reward for sharing content
* No ownership in creator success
* Passive consumption
* Limited ways to support creators

### 2.3 Market Gap

No platform today:

* rewards fans for helping creators grow
* combines learning + earning + community
* replaces algorithm dependence with human growth

---

## 3. Solution Summary

### 3.1 Core Solution

HeyBirdy introduces a **community-driven growth flywheel**:

```
Creator publishes
‚Üí Fans engage
‚Üí Fans share
‚Üí New users join
‚Üí Everyone earns
‚Üí Growth compounds
```

Growth is powered by **people**, not feeds.

---

### 3.2 Key Principles

1. Simple signup first
2. Roles unlocked by actions
3. One identity, multiple capabilities
4. Every action creates value
5. Rewards are always visible

---

## 4. Target Users & Personas

### 4.1 Personas

* **Creator (Alex):** Wants predictable income & community-led growth
* **Affiliate (Jamie):** Wants to earn by sharing trusted content
* **Member/Learner (Taylor):** Wants to learn, engage, and be rewarded

> Personas are **starting states**, not permanent roles.

---

## 5. User Identity & Role Model

### 5.1 Identity Model

* One account per user
* No role selection at signup
* Capabilities unlock via actions

### 5.2 Progressive Role Activation

| Action                  | Capability Unlocked |
| ----------------------- | ------------------- |
| Watching / learning     | Member (default)    |
| Clicking ‚ÄúShare & Earn‚Äù | Affiliate           |
| Clicking ‚ÄúPost content‚Äù | Creator             |

Users can hold **multiple capabilities simultaneously**.

---

## 6. Core Features & Requirements

---

### 6.1 Authentication & Onboarding

**Goal:** Zero friction entry

#### Functional Requirements

* Social login (Google, Apple, Email)
* No role selection at signup
* Immediate access to content feed
* Inline prompts for role activation

#### Success Criteria

* Signup < 30 seconds
* First content view < 1 minute

---

### 6.2 Content Platform (Creator Capability)

#### Features

* Multi-format content upload (video, text, course)
* Free previews
* Pricing (free, paid, subscription)
* Affiliate enable/disable per content
* Content analytics

#### Creator Activation

Triggered when user clicks **‚ÄúPost content‚Äù**

---

### 6.3 Affiliate System (Affiliate Capability)

#### Features

* One-click affiliate activation
* Auto-generated unique links
* Real-time tracking (clicks, conversions)
* Commission calculation
* Leaderboards

#### Affiliate Activation

Triggered when user clicks **‚ÄúShare & Earn‚Äù**

---

### 6.4 Learning & Engagement (Member Capability)

#### Features

* Personalized content feed
* Progress tracking
* Points for engagement
* Skill badges
* Comments & discussions

Member capability is **always on by default**.

---

### 6.5 Monetization Engine

#### Revenue Streams

* Content sales
* Subscriptions
* Affiliate commissions
* Tips / rewards

#### Split Payments

* Creator
* Affiliate
* Platform

Earnings update in real time.

---

### 6.6 Community & Social Layer

#### Features

* Follow creators
* Comments & replies
* Leaderboards
* Live sessions (Phase 2)

Community interaction is tied to:

* visibility
* reputation
* rewards

---

## 7. Key User Flows

---

### 7.1 First-Time User Flow

```
Signup
‚Üí Explore content
‚Üí Watch preview
‚Üí Engage
‚Üí See ‚ÄúShare & Earn‚Äù
‚Üí Take action
```

---

### 7.2 Affiliate Conversion Flow

```
Watch content
‚Üí Click ‚ÄúShare & Earn‚Äù
‚Üí Link generated
‚Üí Share externally
‚Üí Conversion tracked
‚Üí Earnings credited
```

---

### 7.3 Creator Activation Flow

```
Explore platform
‚Üí Click ‚ÄúPost content‚Äù
‚Üí Complete profile
‚Üí Upload content
‚Üí Enable affiliates
```

---

## 8. Non-Functional Requirements

### Performance

* Page load < 2s
* Real-time earnings updates
* Scalable to 100k+ users

### Security

* Secure payments
* Fraud prevention
* Data privacy compliance

### Usability

* Mobile-first
* Simple language
* No blocked actions without explanation

---

## 9. Metrics & Success Criteria

### Activation Metrics

* % users viewing content on day 1
* Time to first share
* Time to first earning

### Growth Metrics

* Viral coefficient
* Affiliate participation rate
* Creator revenue stability

### Retention Metrics

* Weekly active users
* Repeat sharing
* Community engagement

---

## 10. Out of Scope (MVP)

* Native mobile apps
* Advanced AI content generation
* Enterprise tools
* Crypto / Web3

---

## 11. Risks & Mitigation

| Risk               | Mitigation             |
| ------------------ | ---------------------- |
| Users don‚Äôt share  | Strong value + rewards |
| Creator inactivity | Community incentives   |
| Fraud              | Tracking & review      |
| Complexity         | Progressive unlocks    |

---

## 12. Product Principles (Non-Negotiable)

1. No forced roles
2. No passive users
3. No hidden rewards
4. No algorithm mystery
5. No unpaid contribution

---

## 13. Final Product Definition

> **HeyBirdy is a creator growth platform where learning, sharing, and earning happen together ‚Äî and where communities replace algorithms as the engine of growth.**

